# Privacy Policy for Sequential Calculator

*Last updated: May 30, 2026*

This Privacy Policy explains how Sequential Calculator collects, uses, and protects user information.

## 1. Information We Collect

Sequential Calculator is a simple calculator application and does not intentionally collect personally identifiable information from users.

Depending on how the application is hosted or used, limited technical information may automatically be collected by google play services and third-party services such as:

* Browser type
* Device information
* IP address
* Usage statistics
* Error logs
* Analytics

## 2. How Information Is Used

Any automatically collected information may be used only for:

* Improving application performance
* Fixing bugs and technical issues
* Monitoring usage and stability

## 3. Cookies and Tracking

Sequential Calculator itself does not use cookies or tracking technologies directly.

## 4. Third-Party Services

This project may rely on third-party platforms or services, including:

* GitHub (https://github.com)

These services may collect information according to their own privacy policies.

## 5. Data Security

Reasonable efforts are made to keep the project secure. However, no method of electronic storage or internet transmission is completely secure.

## 6. Children's Privacy

Sequential Calculator is not directed toward children under the age of 13 and does not knowingly collect personal information from children.

